# Pi `config.txt` (repo copy) — hardware expectations

## Enabled in tracked `config.txt`
- **`dtparam=spi=on`** — SPI for MCP2515 and similar.
- **`dtoverlay=mcp2515-can0,oscillator=16000000,interrupt=25`** — MCP2515 on SPI, **16 MHz** crystal, IRQ on **BCM GPIO 25** (not physical pin number).
- **`dtoverlay=spi-bcm2835-overlay`**, **`dtparam=audio=on`**, **`dtoverlay=disable-bt`** (Pi 4–style BT off for UART use cases), **`enable_uart=1`**, **`gpu_mem=256`**.

## App vs GPIO
- Qt code generally uses **kernel interfaces** (`can0`, serial ports, backlight sysfs), not direct GPIO bit-bang; pin usage follows **device tree / overlays** on the SD card image (Bookworm may use **`/boot/firmware/config.txt`** on device).

## `fixcan.sh` note
- Script references **alternate MCP2515 line / IRQ 24** — deployment-specific; compare to active **`config.txt`** on the Pi.
